"indicates user-space supports and wants to use 802.1X driver offload of 4-"
"way handshake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3580
msgid "``edmg``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3581
msgid ""
"define the EDMG channels. This may specify multiple channels and bonding "
"options for the driver to choose from, based on BSS configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3523
msgid ""
"This structure provides information needed to complete IEEE 802.11 "
"authentication and association."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3670
msgid "PMK Security Association"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3676
msgid "The AP's BSSID (may be ``NULL``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3676
msgid "``pmkid``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3677
msgid "The identifier to refer a PMKSA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3677
msgid "``pmk``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3678
msgid ""
"The PMK for the PMKSA identified by **pmkid**. This is used for key "
"derivation by a FILS STA. Otherwise, ``NULL``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3679
msgid "``pmk_len``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3680
msgid ""
"Length of the **pmk**. The length of **pmk** can differ depending on the "
"hash algorithm used to generate this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3682
msgid ""
"SSID to specify the ESS within which a PMKSA is valid when using FILS cache "
"identifier (may be ``NULL``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3684
msgid "Length of the **ssid** in octets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3684
msgid "``cache_id``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3685
msgid ""
"2-octet cache identifier advertized by a FILS AP identifying the scope of "
"PMKSA. This is valid only if **ssid_len** is non-zero (may be ``NULL``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3687
msgid "``pmk_lifetime``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3688
msgid ""
"Maximum lifetime for PMKSA in seconds (dot11RSNAConfigPMKLifetime) or 0 if "
"not specified. The configured PMKSA must not be used for PMKSA caching after "
"expiration and any keys derived from this PMK become invalid on expiration, "
"i.e., the current association must be dropped if the PMK used for it expires."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3693
msgid "``pmk_reauth_threshold``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3694
msgid ""
"Threshold time for reauthentication (percentage of PMK lifetime, "
"dot11RSNAConfigPMKReauthThreshold) or 0 if not specified. Drivers are "
"expected to trigger a full authentication instead of using this PMKSA for "
"caching when reassociating to a new BSS after this threshold to generate a "
"new PMK before the current one expires."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:3671
msgid ""
"This structure is passed to the set/del_pmksa() method for PMKSA caching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4663
msgid "backend description for wireless configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4676
msgid "``suspend``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4677
msgid ""
"wiphy device needs to be suspended. The variable **wow** will be ``NULL`` or "
"contain the enabled Wake-on-Wireless triggers that are configured for the "
"device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4679
msgid "``resume``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4680
msgid "wiphy device needs to be resumed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4680
msgid "``set_wakeup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4681
msgid ""
"Called when WoWLAN is enabled/disabled, use this callback to call "
"device_set_wakeup_enable() to enable/disable wakeup from the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4684
msgid "``add_virtual_intf``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4685
msgid ""
"create a new virtual interface with the given name, must set the struct "
"wireless_dev's iftype. Beware: You must create the new netdev in the wiphy's "
"network namespace! Returns the struct wireless_dev, or an ERR_PTR. For P2P "
"device wdevs, the driver must also set the address member in the wdev. This "
"additionally holds the RTNL to be able to do netdev changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4691
msgid "``del_virtual_intf``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4692
msgid ""
"remove the virtual interface This additionally holds the RTNL to be able to "
"do netdev changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4694
msgid "``change_virtual_intf``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4695
msgid ""
"change type/configuration of virtual interface, keep the struct "
"wireless_dev's iftype updated. This additionally holds the RTNL to be able "
"to do netdev changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4698
msgid "``add_intf_link``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4699
msgid ""
"Add a new MLO link to the given interface. Note that the wdev->link[] data "
"structure has been updated, so the new link address is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4701
msgid "``del_intf_link``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4702
msgid "Remove an MLO link from the given interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4703
msgid "``add_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4704
msgid ""
"add a key with the given parameters. **mac_addr** will be ``NULL`` when "
"adding a group key. **link_id** will be -1 for non-MLO connection. For MLO "
"connection, **link_id** will be >= 0 for group key and -1 for pairwise key, "
"**mac_addr** will be peer's MLD address for MLO pairwise key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4708
msgid "``get_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4709
msgid ""
"get information about the key with the given parameters. **mac_addr** will "
"be ``NULL`` when requesting information for a group key. All pointers given "
"to the **callback** function need not be valid after it returns. This "
"function should return an error if it is not possible to retrieve the key, -"
"ENOENT if it doesn't exist. **link_id** will be -1 for non-MLO connection. "
"For MLO connection, **link_id** will be >= 0 for group key and -1 for "
"pairwise key, **mac_addr** will be peer's MLD address for MLO pairwise key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4717
msgid "``del_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4718
msgid ""
"remove a key given the **mac_addr** (``NULL`` for a group key) and "
"**key_index**, return -ENOENT if the key doesn't exist. **link_id** will be "
"-1 for non-MLO connection. For MLO connection, **link_id** will be >= 0 for "
"group key and -1 for pairwise key, **mac_addr** will be peer's MLD address "
"for MLO pairwise key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4723
msgid "``set_default_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4724
msgid ""
"set the default key on an interface. **link_id** will be >= 0 for MLO "
"connection and -1 for non-MLO connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4726
msgid "``set_default_mgmt_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4727
msgid ""
"set the default management frame key on an interface. **link_id** will be >= "
"0 for MLO connection and -1 for non-MLO connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4729
msgid "``set_default_beacon_key``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:4730
msgid ""
