#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:48: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:9039
msgid ""
"This function may be called with the driver passing either the BSSID of the "
"new AP or passing the bss entry to avoid a race in timeout of the bss entry. "
"It should be called by the underlying driver whenever it roamed from one AP "
"to another while connected. Drivers which have roaming implemented in "
"firmware should pass the bss entry to avoid a race in bss entry timeout "
"where the bss entry of the new AP is seen in the driver, but gets timed out "
"by the time it is accessed in __cfg80211_roamed() due to delay in scheduling "
"rdev->event_work. In case of any failures, the reference is released either "
"in cfg80211_roamed() or in __cfg80211_romed(), Otherwise, it will be "
"released while disconnecting from the current bss."
msgstr ""

