msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:149: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:7861
msgid "the custom regulatory domain to use for this wiphy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:149: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:7862
msgid ""
"Drivers can sometimes have custom regulatory domains which do not apply to a "
"specific country. Drivers can use this to apply such custom regulatory "
"domains. This routine must be called prior to wiphy registration. The custom "
"regulatory domain will be trusted completely and as such previous default "
"channel settings will be disregarded. If no rule is found for a channel on "
"the regulatory domain the channel will be disabled. Drivers using this for a "
"wiphy should also set the wiphy flag REGULATORY_CUSTOM_REG or cfg80211 will "
"set it for the wiphy that called this helper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:149: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:7877
msgid "get regulatory information for the given frequency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/80211/cfg80211:149: ../include/net/cfg80211.h:7878
